http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Leopard-skin-seized-one-held/article13993117.ece

A tribal man was on Sunday arrested after the police allegedly seized a leopard skin from him at Karapalli village in the Malkangiri district.Acting on a tip-off, forest department officials, posing as prospective buyers of animal skin and body parts, approached Sanyasi Naik, Divisional Forest Officer (Malkangiri), T. Ashok Kumar, said.Sanyasi was caught when he showed them the leopard skin, valued at over Rs.1 lakh.The accused has admitted to having killed the leopard about two months ago. - PTI